# CLAUDE.local.md — <your-name>'s working quick-reference

> This file is **gitignored**. It holds project-specific context that's only useful to your own setup — current skill inventory, codebase shortcuts, team conventions. Generic maintenance rules live in `CLAUDE.md`.
>
> To start: `cp CLAUDE.local.md.example CLAUDE.local.md`, then fill it in.

## Current skill inventory

List every skill currently in `skills/` and one line on when it applies. The AI reads this to decide which skill to pull on a given turn — be specific.

| Skill                          | Apply when...                                            |
|--------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| `<your-skill-name>`            | <one-line "when it applies" hook>                        |
| `<your-skill-name>`            | <one-line "when it applies" hook>                        |

## Codebase shortcuts

Project-specific commands, paths, conventions that the AI should know without being told every time. Examples:

- `<repo-name>` deploy command: `<command>`
- API tier / rate-limit quirks: `<note>`
- Sprint structure / current focus: `<note>`

## Notes that don't belong in a skill (yet)

Use this section as a holding area for observations that aren't yet durable enough to be a skill but are worth not losing. When a note stabilises into a recurring pattern, promote it into the relevant `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` per `CLAUDE.md` decision rule.
